metadata:

hadiths[158]{hadithnumber,arabicnumber,text,reference_book,reference_hadith,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro,urdu,chapter_title_arabic}:
3801,1511.01,Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) reported that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade (two types of transactions) Mulamasa and Munabadha,21,1,,,,,,محمد بن یحییٰ بن حبان نے اعرج سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی کہ رسول اللہ صلی,3801,
3802,1511.02,Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) reported like this from Allah's Messenger (ﷺ),21,2,,,,,,ابوزناد نے اعرج سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے اور انہوں نے نبی صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم سے ,3802,
3803,1511.03,Abu Huraira reported from Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) a hadith like this through another chain cf transmitters,21,3,,,,,,حفص بن عاصم نے حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے اور انہوں نے نبی صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم سے اسی کے مانند روا,3803,
3804,1511.04,A hadith like this has been narrated on the authority of Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) through another chain of transmitters,21,4,,,,,,ابوصالح نے حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے اور انہوں نے نبی صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم سے اسی کے مانند روایت ک,3804,
3805,1511.05,"Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) reported:Two types of trarisactions have been forbidden (by the Holy Prophet), al-Mlulamasa and al-Munabadha. As far as Mulamasa transaction is concerned, it is that every one of them (the parties entering into transaction) should touch the garment of the other without careful consideration, and al-Munabadha is that every one of them should throw his cloth to the other and one of them should not see the cloth of his friend",21,5,,,,,,عمرو بن دینار نے عطاء بن میناء سے روایت کی کہ انہوں نے ان  ( عطاء )  کو حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ س,3805,
3806,1512.01,"Abu Sa'id al-Khudri (Allah be pleased with him) reported:Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade us (from), two types of business transactions and two ways of dressing. He forbade Mulamasa and Munabadha in transactions. Mulamasa means the touching of another's garment with his hand, whether at night or by day, without turning it over except this much. Munabadha means that a man throws his garment to another and the other throws his garment, and thus confirming their contract without the inspection of mutual agreement",21,6,,,,,,"یونس نے مجھے ابن شہاب سے خبر دی ،  انہوں نے کہا :  مجھے عامر بن سعد بن ابی وقاص نے بتایا کہ حضرت ابو",3806,
3807,1512.02,This hadith has been narrated on the authority of Ibn Shihab through the same chain of transmitters,21,7,,,,,,صالح نے ابن شہاب سے اسی سند کے ساتھ یہی حدیث بیان کی,3807,
3808,1513,"Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) reported that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade a transaction determined by throwing stones, and the type which involves some uncertainty",21,8,,,,,,"حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے ،  انہوں نے کہا :  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے کنکر پھینک",3808,
3809,1514.01,Abdullah (b. 'Umar) (Allah be pleased with him) said that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade the transaction called habal al-habala,21,9,,,,,,لیث نے نافع سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت عبداللہ  ( بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ )  سے اور انہوں نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ,3809,
3810,1514.02,Ibn 'Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported that the people of pre-Islamic days used to sell the meat of the slaughtered camel up to habal al-habala. And habal al-habala implies that a she-camel should give birth and then the (born one should grow young) and become pregnant. Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade them that (this transaction),21,10,,,,,,"عبیداللہ سے روایت ہے ،  انہوں نے کہا :  مجھے نافع نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے خبر دی ،  انہوں نے",3810,
3811,1412.05,"Ibn 'Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as having said this:One amongst you should not enter into a transaction when another is bargaining",21,11,,,,,,امام مالک نے نافع سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی کہ رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وس,3811,
3812,1412.06,"Ibn 'Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:A person should not enter into a transaction when his brother is already making a transaction and he should not make a proposal of marriage when his brother has already made a proposal except when he gives permission",21,12,,,,,,"عبیداللہ نے کہا :  مجھے نافع نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے خبر دی ،  انہوں نے نبی صلی اللہ علیہ وس",3812,
3813,1515.01,"Abu Huraira reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:A Muslim should not purchase (in opposition) to his brother",21,13,,,,,,اسماعیل بن جعفر نے ہمیں علاء سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے اپنے والد  ( عبدالرحمٰن )  سے ،  انہوں نے ح,3813,
3814,1515.02,This hadith has been narrated on the authority of Abu Huraira through another chain of transmitters but with a slight change of words,21,14,,,,,,"احمد بن ابراہیم دورقی نے مجھے یہی حدیث بیان کی ،  کہا :  مجھے عبدالصمد نے حدیث بیان کی ،  کہا :  ہمی",3814,
3815,1515.03,"Abu Huraira reported Allah's Messenger (may peace'be upon him) as saying:Do not go out to meet riders to enter into transaction with them; none of you must buy in opposition to another, nor must you bid against one another; a townsman must not sell for a man from the desert, and do not tie up udders of carnels and sheep, and he who buys them after that has been done has two courses open to him: after he has milked them he may keep them if he is pleased with them, or he may return them along with a sit of dates if he is displeased with them",21,15,,,,,,"اعرج نے حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی کہ رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا :   "" بیع ک",3815,
3816,1515.04,"Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) reported that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade the (people) meeting the caravan (for entering into business transaction with them), and the selling of goods by a townsman on behalf of a man of the desert, and seeking by a woman the divorce of her sister (from her husband), and outbidding (against one another), and tying up the udders (of animals), and buying of (things) in opposition to one's brother",21,16,,,,,,"معاذ عنبری نے کہا :  ہمیں شعبہ نے عدی بن ثابت سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے ابوحازم سے اور انہوں نے حض",3816,
3817,1515.05,This hadith has been narrated through another chain of transmitters,21,17,,,,,,"غندر ،  وہب بن جریر اور عبدالصمد بن عبدالوارث سب نے کہا :  ہمیں شعبہ نے اسی سند کے ساتھ شعبہ سے روای",3817,
3818,1516,Ibn Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade the outbidding (against another),21,18,,,,,,حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے  ( خریدنے کے ارادے کے بغیر ,3818,
3819,1517.01,"Ibn 'Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:Do not go out to meet merchandise in the way, (wait) until it is brought into the market. This hadith has been reported on the authority of Ibn Numair but with a slight change of words",21,19,,,,,,ابن ابی زائدہ ،  یحییٰ بن سعید اور  ( عبداللہ )  ابن نمیر ،  ان سب نے عبیداللہ سے ،  انہوں نے نافع س,3819,
3820,1517.02,This hadith has been reported on the authority of 'Ubaidullah,21,20,,,,,,امام مالک نے نافع سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے اور انہوں نے نبی صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم سے,3820,
3821,1518,"Abdullah (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Apostle (ﷺ) as saying:Do not meet the traders (in the way)",21,21,,,,,,حضرت عبداللہ رضی اللہ عنہ نے نبی صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم سے روایت کی کہ نبی صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے  ( راست,3821,
3822,1519.01,"Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Messenger (may peace he upon him) as saying:Do not meet the merchandise (in the way)",21,22,,,,,,ہُشَیم نے ہمیں ہشام سے خبر دی ،  انہوں نے ابن سیرین سے اور انہوں نے حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے رو,3822,
3823,1519.02,"Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:Do not meet the merchant in the way and enter into business transaction with him, and whoever meets him and buys from him (and in case it is done, see) that when the owner of (merchandise) comes into the market (and finds that he has been paid less price) he has the option (to declare the transaction null and void)",21,23,,,,,,"ابن جریج نے کہا :  مجھے ہشام قردوسی نے ابن سیرین سے خبر دی ،  انہوں نے کہا :  میں نے حضرت ابوہریرہ ر",3823,
3824,1520,"Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) reported it directly from Allah's Apostle (ﷺ):The townsman'should not sell for a man from the desert (with a view to taking advantage of his ignorance of the market conditions of the city). And Zuhair reported from the Prophet (ﷺ) that he forbade the townsman to sell on behalf of the man from the desert",21,24,,,,,,"ابوبکر بن ابی شیبہ ،  عمرو ناقد اور زُہَیر بن حرب نے کہا :  ہمیں سفیان نے زہری سے حدیث بیان کی ،  ان",3824,
3825,1521,"Ibn 'Abbas (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:The riders (carrying merchandise) should not be met in the way, and townsman should not sell for a man of the desert. The narrator reported. I said to Ibn 'Abbas: What do these words really imply-"" The townsman for the man of the desert""? He said: That he should work as a broker on his behalf",21,25,,,,,,"طاوس کے بیٹے نے اپنے والد سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابن عباس رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی ،  انہوں نے کہا :  ر",3825,
3826,1522.01,"Jabir (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:The townsman should not sell for a man from the desert, leave the people alone, Allah will give them provision from one another. Yahya reported it with a slight change of words",21,26,,,,,,"یحییٰ بن یحییٰ تمیمی اور احمد بن یونس نے کہا :  ہمیں ابوخثیمہ زہیر نے حدیث سنائی ،  کہا :  ہمیں ابوز",3826,
3827,1522.02,Jabir (Allah be pleased with him) reported a similar hadith from Allah's Apostle (ﷺ) through another chain of transmitters,21,27,,,,,,سفیان بن عیینہ نے ہمیں ابوزہیر سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے حضرت جابر رضی اللہ عنہ سے ،  انہوں نے نبی,3827,
3828,1523.01,"Anas b. Malik (Allah be pleased with him) reported:We were forbidden that a townsman should sell for a man of the desert, even if he is his brother or father",21,28,,,,,,"یونس نے ابن سیرین سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت انس بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی ،  انہوں نے کہا :  ہمیں م",3828,
3829,1523.02,"Anas b. Malik (Allah be pleased with him) said:We were forbidden that a townsman should sell for a man of the desert",21,29,,,,,,"ابن عون نے ہمیں محمد  ( بن سیرین )  سے حدیث بیان کی ،  کہا :  حضرت انس بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ نے کہا :",3829,
3830,1524.01,"Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Messenger (may peace be'upon him) as saying:He who bought a goat having its udder tied up should go back with it, milk it, and, if he is satisfied with its milk, he should retair it, otherwise he should return it along with a sa' of dates",21,30,,,,,,موسیٰ بن یسار نے حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی ،  انہوں نے کہا ،  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ و,3830,
3831,1524.02,"Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:He who buys a goat with its udder tied up has the option to retain the goat if he so desires or return it within three days, and in case he returns it he should do so along with a sa' of dates",21,31,,,,,,سہیل کے والد  ( ابوصالح )  نے حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی کہ رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم,3831,
3832,1524.03,"Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Apostle (ﷺ) as saying:lie who buys a goat having its udder tied up has the option to return it within three days. If he returns it he should pay a sa' of dates. Wheat is not essential",21,32,,,,,,قرہ نے ہمیں محمد  ( بن سیرین )  سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے اور انہوں ,3832,
3833,1524.04,"Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:He who buys a goat having its udder tied up has two courses left for him. He may retain it, and if he desires may return it along with a sa' of dates and not wheat",21,33,,,,,,سفیان نے ہمیں ایوب سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے محمد  ( بن سیرین )  سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی ,3833,
3834,1524.05,"Ayyub narrated with the same chain of transmitters but with this change of words:"" He who buys a goat has the option",21,34,,,,,,"عبدالوہاب نے ایوب سے اسی سند کے ساتھ حدیث بیان کی ،  لیکن انہوں نے کہا :   "" جس نے  ( دودھ روکی ہوئی",3834,
3835,1524.06,"Hammam b. Munabbih said:Out of the ahadith which Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) reported to us from Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) one is this that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) said: If one among you buys a she-camel having its udder tied up he has the two options for him after milking it either (to retain it) or return it with a sa' of dates",21,35,,,,,,"ہمام بن منبہ سے روایت ہے ،  انہوں نے کہا :  یہ احادیث ہیں جو ہمیں حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ نے رسول",3835,
3837,1525.01,"Ibn Abbas (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:He who buys foodgrain should not sell it until he has taken possession of it",21,36,,,,,,سفیان بن عیینہ اور سفیان ثوری نے عمرو بن دینار سے اسی سند کے ساتھ اسی کے مطابق روایت کی,3837,
3838,1525.02,A hadith like this has been narrated through the same chain of transmitters,21,37,,,,,,معمر نے ابن طاوس سے خبر دی ،  انہوں نے اپنے والد سے اور انہوں نے حضرت ابن عباس رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت,3838,
3839,1525.03,"Ibn Abbas (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:He who buys food-rain should not sell it until he has taken possession of it. Ibn Abbas (Allah be pleased with them) said: I regard everything like food (so far as this principle is concerned)",21,38,,,,,,"ابوبکر بن ابی شیبہ ،  ابو کُرَیب اور اسحاق بن ابراہیم نے ہمیں حدیث بیان کی  ۔  ۔  اسحاق نے کہا :  ہم",3839,
3840,1526.01,"Ibn 'Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:He who buys foodgrain should not sell it until he has taken full possession of it",21,40,,,,,,"عبداللہ بن مسلمہ قعنبی نے ہمیں حدیث سنائی ،  کہا :  ہمیں مالک نے حدیث سنائی ۔  اور یحییٰ بن یحییٰ نے",3840,
3841,1527.01,"Ibn Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported:We used to buy foodgrains during the lifetime of Allah's Messenger (ﷺ). He (the Holy Prophet) would then send to us one who commanded us to take them (the foodgrains) to a place other than the one where we had bought them before we sold it",21,41,,,,,,"یحییٰ بن یحییٰ نے سابقہ سند کے ساتھ حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی ،  انہوں نے کہا :  رسول ال",3841,
3843,1526.03,"Ibn 'Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:He who bought foodgrain should not sell it until he had taken full possession of it (after measuring it)",21,43,,,,,,"نیز انہوں  ( حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ )  نے کہا :  ہم اہل قافلہ سے بغیر ماپ  ( اور وزن )  کے غلہ خر",3843,
3844,1526.04,"Ibn 'Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying,:He who bought foodgrain should not sell it until he had taken possession of it",21,44,,,,,,عمر بن محمد نے نافع سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی کہ اللہ کے رسول صلی ,3844,
3846,1527.02,,21,42,,,,,,معمر نے زہری سے ،  انہوں نے سالم سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی کہ رسول اللہ ص,3846,
3847,1527.04,"Salim b. 'Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) reported his father havingsaid this:I saw people being beaten during the lifetime of Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) in case they bought the foodgrain in bulk, and then sold them at that spot before taking it to their places. This hadith is narrated on the authority of 'Ubaidullah b. Abdullah b. 'Umar through another chain of transmitters (and the words are):"" His father (Ibn 'Umar) used to buy foodgrains in bulk and then carried them to his people",21,46,,,,,,"یونس نے مجھے ابن شہاب  ( زہری )  سے خبر دی ،  انہوں نے کہا :  مجھے سالم بن عبداللہ نے بتایا کہ ان کے",3847,
3848,1528.01,"Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:He who bought foodgrain should not sell it until he had measured it. In the narration of Abu Bakr there the word is Ibta' instead of Ishtara",21,47,,,,,,"ابوبکر بن ابی شیبہ ،  ابن نمیر اور ابو کریب نے کہا :  ہمیں زید بن حباب نے ضحاک بن عثمان سے حدیث بیان",3848,
3849,1528.02,"Abu Huraira (Allah be please with him) is reported to have said to Marwan:Have you made lawful the transactions involving interest? Thereupon Marwan said: I have not done that. Thereupon Abu Huraira (ﷺ) said: You have made lawful the transactions with the help of documents only, whereas Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade the transaction of foodgrains until full possession is taken of them. Marwan then addressed the people and forbade them to enter into such transactions (as are done with the help of documents). Sulaiman said: I saw the sentinels snatching (these documents) from the people",21,48,,,,,,"عبداللہ بن حارث مخزومی نے ہمیں خبر دی ،  کہا :  ہمیں ضحاک بن عثمان نے بکیر بن عبداللہ بن اشج سے حدیث",3849,
3850,1529,"Jabir b. Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:When you purchase foodgrains, do not sell them until you have taken possession of them",21,49,,,,,,"حضرت جابر بن عبداللہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم فرمایا کرتے تھے :   "" جب ",3850,
3851,1530.01,Jabir b. Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) is reported to have said that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade the sale of a heap of dates the weight of which is unknown in accordance with the known weight of dates,21,50,,,,,,"روح بن عبادہ نے ہمیں حدیث بیان کی ،  کہا :  ہمیں ابن جریج نے ابوزبیر سے خبر دی ،  انہوں نے جابر بن ع",3851,
3852,1530.02,This hadith is narrated on the authority of Jabir b. Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) but with this variation that no mention is made of the dates (which one finds) at the end of the previous hadith,21,51,,,,,,"روح بن عبادہ نے ہمیں حدیث بیان کی ،  کہا :  ہمیں ابن جریج نے ابوزبیر سے خبر دی ،  انہوں نے جابر بن ع",3852,
3853,1531.01,"Ibn 'Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:Both parties in a business transaction have the right to annul it so long as they have not separated; except in transactions which have been made subject to the right of parties to annul them",21,52,,,,,,امام مالک نے نافع سے اور انہوں نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی کہ اللہ کے رسول صلی اللہ علی,3853,
3854,1531.02,This hadith has been narrated on the authority of Ibn 'Umar (Allah be pleased with them) through another chain of transmitters,21,53,,,,,,عبیداللہ ،  ایوب ،  یحییٰ بن سعید اور ضحاک نے نافع سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے اور ا,3854,
3855,1531.03,"Ibn 'Umar (Allah be pleased with thcm) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:When two persons enter into a transaction, each of them has the right to annul it so long as they are not separated and are together (at the place of transaction) ; or if one gives the other the right (to annul the transaction) But if one gives the other the option, the transaction is made on this condition (i. e. one has the right to annul the transaction), it becomes binding. And if they are separated after they have made the bargain and none of them annulled it, even then the transaction is binding",21,54,,,,,,لیث نے ہمیں نافع سے خبر دی ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے اور انہوں نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ ,3855,
3856,1531.04,"Abdullah b. 'Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:When two persons enter into a transac. tion, each one of them has the right to annul it so long as they are not separated, or their transaction gives one another (as a condition) the right of annulling, and if their transaction, has the right of annulling it the transaction becomes binding. Ibn Abi Umar made this addition that whenever he (Ibn Umar) entered into a transaction with a person with the intention of not breaking it, he walked a while and then returned to him",21,55,,,,,,"زہیر بن حرب اور ابن ابی عمر دونوں نے سفیان سے روایت کی ۔  زہیر نے کہا :  ہمیں سفیان بن عیینہ نے ابن ",3856,
3857,1531.05,"Ibn Umar reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:There is no transaction between two persons entering a transaction until they separate, but only when there is an option to annul it",21,56,,,,,,عبداللہ بن دینار سے روایت ہے کہ انہوں نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے سنا وہ کہہ رہے تھے ۔  رسول الل,3857,
3858,1532.01,"Hakim b. Hazim (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:Both parties in a business transaction have the right to annul it so long as they have not separated; and if they speak the truth and make everything clear they will be blessed in their transaction; but if they tell a lie and conceal anything the blessing on their transaction will be blotted out",21,57,,,,,,ابوخلیل نے عبداللہ بن حارث سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت حکیم بن حزام رضی اللہ عنہ سے اور انہوں نے نبی صلی الل,3858,
3859,1532.02,"A hadith like this has been transmitted on the authority of Hakim b. Hizam (Imam Muslim) said:Hakim b. Hizam was born inside the Ka'ba and lived for one hundred and twenty years",21,58,,,,,,"ابوتیاح سے روایت ہے ،  انہوں نے کہا :  میں نے عبداللہ بن حارث سے سنا ،  وہ حکیم بن حزام رضی اللہ عنہ",3859,
3860,1533.01,"Abdullah b. Dinar narrated that he heard Ibn 'Umar (Allah be pleased with them) saying:A man mentioned to the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) that he was deceived in a business transaction, whereupon Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) said: When you enter into a transaction, say: There should be no attempt to deceive",21,59,,,,,,اسماعیل بن جعفر نے عبداللہ بن دینار سے روایت کی ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے سنا ،  وہ ک,3860,
3861,1533.02,"This hadith has been narrated on the authority of 'Abdullah b. Dinar with the same chain of transmitters but these words are not found in it."" When he buys he should say:There should be no attempt to deceive",21,60,,,,,,سفیان اور شعبہ دونوں نے عبداللہ بن دینار سے اسی سند کے ساتھ اسی کے مانند حدیث بیان کی ،  لیکن ان دون,3861,
3862,1534.01,"Ibn 'Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade the sale of fruits until they were clearly in good condition, he forbade it both to the seller and to the buyer",21,61,,,,,,امام مالک نے نافع سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی کہ اللہ کے رسول صلی اللہ علیہ,3862,
3863,1534.02,Another chain on the authority of Ibn 'Umar narrated the same as the above hadith,21,62,,,,,,عبیداللہ نے ہمیں نافع سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے ،  انہوں نے نبی صلی ا,3863,
3864,1535,"Ibn 'Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade the sale of palm-trees (i. e. their trults) until the dates began to ripen, and ears of corn until they were white and were safe from blight. He forbade the seller and the buyer",21,63,,,,,,حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے کھجور کی بیع سے منع فرمایا ,3864,
3865,1534.03,"Ibn Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:Do not buy fruit until its good condition becomes clear, and (the danger) of blight is no more. He said: Its good condition becoming clear implies that it becomes red or yellow",21,64,,,,,,جریر نے ہمیں یحییٰ بن سعید سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے نافع سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ,3865,
3866,1534.04,"This hadith is reported or the authority of Yahya with the same chain of transmitters up to"" until its good condition becomes clear,"" but lie did not mention what follows (these words)",21,65,,,,,,"عبدالوہاب نے یحییٰ سے اسی سند کے ساتھ  "" حتیٰ کہ اس کی صلاحیت واضح ہو جائے ""  تک حدیث بیان کی ،  اس ",3866,
3867,1534.05,This hadith has been narrated on the authority of Ibn 'Umar through another chain of transmitters,21,66,,,,,,"ابن ابی فُدیک نے ہمیں حدیث بیان کی ،  کہا :  ہمیں ضحاک نے نافع سے خبر دی ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابن عمر رض",3867,
3868,1534.06,"Nafi, reported on the authority of Ibn Umar (Allah be pleased with them) a hadith like that narrated before",21,67,,,,,,موسیٰ بن عقبہ نے مجھے نافع سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے ،  انہوں نے نبی ,3868,
3869,1534.07,"Ibn Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger' (ﷺ) as saying:Do not buy fruits (on the trees) until their good condition becomes clear",21,68,,,,,,اسماعیل بن جعفر نے عبداللہ بن دینار سے روایت کی کہ انہوں نے ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے سنا ،  انہوں نے ,3869,
3870,1534.08,"In the hadith transmitted on the authority of Shu'ba it was stated that Ibn Umar (Allah be pleased with them) was asked what good condition implied. He said:When (the danger of) blight is no more",21,69,,,,,,سفیان اور شعبہ دونوں نے عبداللہ بن دینار سے اسی سند کے ساتھ حدیث بیان کی ،  شعبہ کی حدیث میں یہ اضاف,3870,
3871,1536.01,Jabir (Allah be pleased with him) reported that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade (or forbade us) the sale of fruits until they are ripe in a good condition,21,70,,,,,,"ابوزبیر نے ہمیں حضرت جابر رضی اللہ عنہ سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے کہا :  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وس",3871,
3872,1536.02,Jabir b. Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbidding the sale of fruit until its good condition is obvious,21,71,,,,,,"عمرو بن دینار نے حدیث بیان کی کہ انہوں نے حضرت جابر بن عبداللہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے سنا وہ کہہ رہے تھے : ",3872,
3873,1537,"Abu Bakhtari reported:I asked Ibn 'Abbas (Allah be pleased with them) about the sale of dates. He said: Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade the sale of dates of the trees until one eats them or they are eaten (i. e. they are fit to be eaten) or until they are weighed (or measured). I said: What does it imply:"" Until it is weighed""? Thereupon a person who was with him (Ibn Abbas) said: Until he is able to keep it with him (after plucking them)",21,72,,,,,,"ابو بختری سے روایت ہے ،  انہوں نے کہا :  میں نے حضرت ابن عباس رضی اللہ عنہ سے کھجور کی بیع کے بارے م",3873,
3874,1538.01,"Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:Do not sell the fruits until their good condition becomes evident",21,73,,,,,,"حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے ،  انہوں نے کہا :  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا :  ",3874,
3875,1534.09,Ibn Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Apostle (ﷺ) forbidding the sale of fruits until their good condition becomes evident and the purchase of dates for dates,21,74,,,,,,"ہمیں یحییٰ بن یحییٰ نے حدیث بیان کی ،  کہا :  ہمیں سفیان بن عیینہ نے زہری سے خبر دی ،  نیز ہمیں ابن ",3875,
3876,1539.01,"Zaid b. Thabit (Allah be pleased with him) said that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) gave a concession in case of the sale known as al-araya, there is an addition of the word an tuba'a in the hadith transmitted by Ibn Numair",21,75,,,,,,"ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ نے کہا :  ہمیں زید بن ثابت نے حدیث بیان کی کہ رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے ب",3876,
3877,1538.02,"Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:Do not buy the fruit until their condition is clear, and do not buy the fresh dates. A hadith like this has been reported by Ibn 'Umar through another chain of transmitters",21,76,,,,,,"ابن شہاب سے روایت ہے ،  انہوں نے کہا :  مجھے سعید بن مسیب اور ابوسلمہ بن عبدالرحمٰن نے حدیث بیان کی ",3877,
3878,1539.02,"Sa'id b. al-Musayyib said that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade the transaction of Af Muzabana and Muhaqala. Muzabana means that fresh dates on the trees should be sold against dry dates. Muhaqala implies that the wheat in the ear should be sold against the wheat and getting the land on rent for the wheat (produced in it). He (the narrator) said that the Prophet (ﷺ) had aid:Do not sell fresh fruits on the trees until their good condition becomes manifest, and do not sell fresh dates on the trees against dry dates. Salim said: Abdullah informed me on the authority of Zaid b. Thabit, Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) having given concession afterwards in case of ariyya transactions by which dry dates can be exchanged with fresh dates, but he did not permit it in other cases",21,77,,,,,,ابن شہاب نے سعید بن مسیب سے روایت کی کہ رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے مزابنہ اور محاقلہ کی بیع سے ,3878,
3879,1539.03,Zaid b. Thabit (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Messenger (may peace he upon him) having given concession in case of 'ariyya for selling dry dates (with) fresh dates after measuring them out,21,78,,,,,,امام مالک نے نافع سے ،  انہوں نے ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت زید بن ثابت رضی اللہ عنہ س,3879,
3880,1539.04,Zaid b. Thabit reported that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) give concession in case of 'ariyya transactions according to which the members of the household give dry dates according to a measure and then eat fresh dates (in exchange for it),21,79,,,,,,"سلیمان بن بلال نے ہمیں یحییٰ بن سعید سے خبر دی کہا :  مجھے نافع نے خبر دی کہ انہوں نے حضرت عبداللہ ب",3880,
3881,1539.05,A hadith like this has been narrated on the authority of Nafi' with the same chain of transmitters,21,80,,,,,,"عبدالوہاب نے ہمیں کہا کہ میں نے یحییٰ بن سعید سے سنا وہ کہہ رہے تھے :  مجھے نافع نے اسی سند سے اسی ک",3881,
3882,1539.06,"Yahya b. Sa'id reported this hadith with the same chain of transmitters but with this change:'Ariyya implies that date-palm trees should be donated to the people and then they sell it with a measure of dry dates",21,81,,,,,,"ہشیم نے ہمیں یحییٰ بن سعید سے اسی سند کے ساتھ خبر دی ،  البتہ انہوں نے کہا :  عریہ سے وہ کھجور کا در",3882,
3883,1539.07,"Zaid b Thabit (Allah be pleased with him) reported that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) gave concession in case of al-'ariyya transactions (for exchanging dates) for dates with measure. Yahya said:'Ariyya implies that a person should buy fresh dates on the tree for his family to eat against a measure of dry dates",21,82,,,,,,لیث نے ہمیں یحییٰ بن سعید سے خبر دی ،  انہوں نے نافع سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ,3883,
3884,1539.08,Zaid b. Thabit (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) granting concession in case of 'ariyya transactions and that implies selling of (dry dates for fresh dates) according to a measure,21,83,,,,,,"عبداللہ بن نمیر نے ہمیں حدیث بیان کی ،  کہا :  ہمیں عبیداللہ نے حدیث سنائی ،  انہوں نے کہا :  مجھے ن",3884,
3885,1539.09,Ubaidullah reported this hadith with a slight change of words on the same authority (as quoted above),21,84,,,,,,یحییٰ بن سعید نے عبیداللہ سے اسی سند کے ساتھ حدیث روایت کی ،  اور  ( فروخت کر دیا جائے کی بجائے )   ,3885,
3886,1539.10,"Nafi, reported this hadith with the same chain of transmitters stating that Allah's Messengtr (ﷺ) granted concession in case of 'ariyya transactions (for exchange of the same commodity) with measure",21,85,,,,,,ایوب نے نافع سے اسی سند کے ساتھ روایت کی کہ رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے عرایا کی بیع میں اس کے ا,3886,
3887,1540.01,"Bashair b. Yasir reported on the authority of some of the Companions of Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) among the members of his family among whom one was Sahl b. Abu Hathma that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade buying of fresh dates against dry dates and that it is Riba and this is Muzabana, but he made an exemption of 'ariyya (donations) of a tree or two in which case the members of a family sell dry dates and buy fresh dates for eating them",21,86,,,,,,سلیمان بن بلال نے ہمیں یحییٰ بن سعید سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے بُشیر بن یسار سے ،  انہوں نے اپنے گ,3887,
3888,1540.02,"Bushair b. Yasar reported on the authority of some of the Companion of Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) that he exempted the transactions, of 'ariyya (from the direct exchange of one kind) after measuring the dry dates (in exchange for fresh dates)",21,87,,,,,,لیث نے ہمیں یحییٰ بن سعید سے خبر دی ،  انہوں نے بُشیر بن یسار سے اور انہوں نے اللہ کے رسول صلی اللہ ,3888,
3889,1540.03,Bushair b. Yasir reported on the authority of some of the Companions of Allah's Messenger (may peace be upon hinn) from among the members of his family that he forbade (the direct exchange of a commodity having different qualities) but with the change that Ishaq and Ibn al-Muthanna used the word Zabn in place of Riba and Ibn Abu 'Umar used the word Riba (interest),21,88,,,,,,محمد بن مثنیٰ ،  اسحاق بن ابراہیم اور ابن ابی عمر سب نے  ( عبدالوہاب )  ثقفی سے روایت کی ،  انہوں نے,3889,
3890,1540.04,A hadith like this has been narrated on the authority of Sahl b. Abu Hathma,21,89,,,,,,سفیان بن عیینہ نے ہمیں یحییٰ بن سعید سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے بشیر بن یسار سے ،  انہوں نے سہل بن ,3890,
3891,1540.05,"Sahl b. Abu Hathma reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) having forbidden Muzabana, i. e. exchange of fresh dates with dry dates. except in case of those to whom donations of some trees have been made. It is for them that concession has been given",21,90,,,,,,"ولید بن کثیر نے کہا :  مجھے بنو حارثہ کے مولیٰ بشیر بن یسار نے حدیث بیان کی کہ رافع بن خدیج اور سہل ",3891,
3892,1541,Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) having given exemption of 'ariyya transactions measuring less than five wasqs or up to five wasqs (the narrator Dawud is in doubt whether it was five or less than five),21,91,,,,,,"یحییٰ بن یحییٰ نے کہا :  میں نے امام مالک سے پوچھا :  کیا آپ کو داود بن حصین نے ابن ابی احمد کے آزاد",3892,
3893,1542.01,"Ibn Umar (Allah be pleased them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) having forbidden Muzabana, and Muzabana implies the selling of fresh dates for dry dates by measuring them out and the selling of raisins by measure for grapes",21,92,,,,,,امام مالک نے نافع سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی کہ رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وس,3893,
3894,1542.02,"Abdullah (b. Umar) reported that Allah's Apostle (ﷺ) forbade Muzabana, i. e. buying of fresh dates (on) the trees for dry dates by measure, and the buying of grapes for raisins by measure and the selling of field of corn for corn by measure",21,93,,,,,,"محمد بن بشیر نے کہا :  ہمیں عبیداللہ نے نافع سے حدیث بیان کی کہ حضرت عبداللہ  ( بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ ",3894,
3895,1542.03,A hadith like this has been narrated on the authority of 'Ubaidullah with the same chain of transmitters,21,94,,,,,,ابن ابی زائدہ نے عبیداللہ سے اسی سند کے ساتھ اسی کے مانند روایت کی,3895,
3896,1542.04,"Ibn 'Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) having forbidden Muzabana, and Muzabana is the selling of dry dates by measure for fresh dates and the selling of raisins by measure for grapes and selling of all Ports of fruits on the basis of calculation",21,95,,,,,,"ابو اسامہ نے ہم سے بیان کیا ،  کہا :  ہمیں عبیداللہ نے نافع سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابن عمر",3896,
3897,1542.05,"Ibn 'Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) having forbidden Muzabana, and Muzabana implies the selling of dry dates for fresh dates on the tree with a definite measure (making it clear) that in case it increases, it belongs to me and if it is less, it is my responsibility",21,96,,,,,,اسماعیل بن ابراہیم نے ہمیں ایوب سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے نافع سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی الل,3897,
3898,1542.06,A hadith like this has been transmitted on the authority of Ayyub,21,97,,,,,,حماد نے ایوب سے اسی سند کے ساتھ اسی کے ہم معنی حدیث بیان کی,3898,
3899,1542.07,"Abdullah (b. Umar) (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) having forbidden Mazabana, and it implies that one should sell the fresh fruits of his orchard (for dry fruits) or, if it is fresh dates, for dry dates with a measure, or if it is grapes for raisins or if it is corn in the field for dry corn with a measure He (the Holy Prophet) in fact forbade all such transactions. Qutaiba has narrated it with a slight variation of words",21,98,,,,,,قتیبہ بن سعید اور محمد بن رُمح نے لیث سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے نافع سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت عبداللہ ر,3899,
3900,1542.08,This hadith has been narrated on the authority of Nafi with another chain of transmitters,21,99,,,,,,یونس ،  ضحاک اور موسیٰ بن عقبہ سب نے نافع سے اسی سند کے ساتھ ان  ( عبیداللہ ،  ایوب اور لیث )  کی حد,3900,
3901,1543.01,"Ibn Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:If anyone buys palm-trees after they have been fecundated the fruit belongs to the seller unless the buyer makes a proviso",21,100,,,,,,"یحییٰ بن یحییٰ نے کہا :  میں نے امام مالک کے سامنے قراءت کی ،  انہوں نے نافع سے اور انہوں نے حضرت اب",3901,
3902,1543.02,"Nafi reported on the authority of Ibn Umar (Allah be pleased with them) that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:Whichever tree is bought with its roots, and if it is fecundatedits fruit would belong to one who has grafted it except when the provision is laid down by the buyer",21,101,,,,,,عبیداللہ نے ہمیں نافع سے حدیث بیان کی اور انہوں نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی کہ رسول الل,3902,
3903,1543.03,"Ibn Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Apostle (ﷺ) as saying:Whosoever grafts the tree and then sells its roots, its fruit will belong to one who grafts it except when provision is laid down by the buyer",21,102,,,,,,لیث نے ہمیں نافع سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی کہ نبی صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے ف,3903,
3904,1543.04,"This hadith has been narrated on the authority of Nafi, with the same chain of transmitters",21,103,,,,,,ایوب نے نافع سے اسی سند کے ساتھ اسی طرح روایت کی,3904,
3905,1543.05,"Abdullah b. Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Massenger (ﷺ) as saying:He who buys a tree after it has been fecundated, its fruit belongs to one who sells it except when the provision has been laid down by the buyer (that it will belong to him), and he who buys a slave, his property belongs to one who sells him except when a provision has been laid down by the buyer (that it will be transferred to him with the slave)",21,104,,,,,,لیث نے ہمیں ابن شہاب سے خبر دی ،  انہوں نے سالم بن عبداللہ بن عمر سے اور انہوں نے حضرت عبداللہ بن عم,3905,
3906,1543.06,A hadith like this has been narrated on the authority of al Zuhri,21,105,,,,,,سفیان بن عیینہ نے زہری سے اسی سند کے ساتھ اسی کے مانند روایت کی,3906,
3907,1543.07,Ibn Umar reported on the authority of his father as Allah's Apostle (ﷺ) saying so,21,106,,,,,,"یونس نے مجھے ابن شہاب سے خبر دی ،  کہا :  مجھے سالم بن عبداللہ بن عمر نے حدیث بیان کی کہ ان کے والد ",3907,
3908,1536.03,"Jabir b. Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) reported that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) had forbidden Muhaqala. and Muzabana, Mukhibara and the sale of fruits until their good condition becomes clear, and (he commanded) that (commodities) should not be sold but for the dinar and dirham except in case of araya",21,107,,,,,,سفیان بن عیینہ نے ہمیں ابن جریج سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے عطاء سے اور انہوں نے حضرت جابر بن عبدالل,3908,
3909,1536.04,Jabir b. 'Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) reported that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade the types of sales as described before,21,108,,,,,,"ابوعاصم نے ہمیں خبر دی ،  کہا :  ہمیں ابن جریج نے عطاء اور ابوزبیر سے خبر دی ،  ان دونوں نے حضرت جاب",3909,
3910,1536.05,"Jabir b. 'Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) reported that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade Mukhabara and Muhaqala, and Muzabana, and the sale of the fruit until it is fit for eating, and its sale but with dirham and dinar. Exception is made in case of 'araya. Ata' said:Jabir explained (these terms) for us. As for Mukhabara it is this that a wasteland is given by a person to another and he makes an investment in it and then gets a share in the produce. According to him (Jabir), Muzabana is the sell of fresh dates on the tree for dry dates with a measure, and Muhaqala in agriculture implies that one should sell the standing crop for grains with a measure",21,109,,,,,,"مخلد بن یزید جزری نے ہمیں خبر دی ،  کہا :  ہمیں ابن جریج نے حدیث سنائی ،  انہوں نے کہا :  مجھے عطاء ",3910,
3911,1536.06,"Jabir b. Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbidding Muhaqala, and Muzabana, and Mukhabara, and the buying of date-palm until its fruit is ripened (ripening means that its colour becomes red or yellow, or it is fit for being eaten). And Muhaqala implies that crops in the field are bought for grains according to a customary measure. Muzabana implies that date-palm should be sold for dry dates by measuring them with wisqs, and al-Mukhabara is (a share), maybe one-third or one-fourth (in produce) or something like it. Zaid (one of the narrators) said to Ata' b. Abu Rabah (the other narrator):Did You bear Jabir b. Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) making a mention of it that he had heard it directly from Allah's Messenger (ﷺ)? He said: Yes",21,110,,,,,,"زید بن ابی انیسہ سے روایت ہے ،  انہوں نے کہا :  ہم سے ابوولید مکی نے حدیث بیان کی جبکہ وہ عطاء بن اب",3911,
3912,1536.07,"Jabir b. Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbidding Muzabana and Muhaqala, and Mukhabara, and the sale of fruits until they are ripe. I (the narrator) said to Sa'id (the other narrator):What does ripening imply? He said: It meant that they become red or become yellow and are fit for eating",21,111,,,,,,"سلیم بن حیان نے ہمیں حدیث بیان کی ،  کہا :  ہمیں سعید بن میناء نے حضرت جابر بن عبداللہ رضی اللہ عنہ ",3912,
3913,1536.08,"Jabir b. Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbidding Muhaqala and Muzabana and Mu'awama and Mukhabara. (One of the narrators) 'said:Sale years ahead is Mu'awama, and making exceptional but he made an exemption of araya",21,112,,,,,,"حماد بن زید نے ہمیں حدیث بیان کی ،  کہا :  ہمیں ایوب نے ابوزبیر اور سعید بن میناء سے حدیث بیان کی ، ",3913,
3914,1536.09,A hadith like this has been narrated on the authority of Jabir (Allah be pleased with him) from Allah's Apostle (ﷺ). but he made no mention of transactions years (ahead) implying Mu'awama,21,113,,,,,,اسماعیل بن علیہ نے ہمیں ایوب سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے ابوزبیر سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت جابر بن عبداللہ,3914,
3915,1536.10,"Jabir b. Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) reported that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade leasing of land, and selling ahead for years and selling of fruits before they become ripe",21,114,,,,,,"رباح بن ابی معروف نے ہمیں حدیث بیان کی ، انہوں نے کہا :  میں نے عطاء سے سنا ،  انہوں نے حضرت جابر بن",3915,
3916,1536.11,Jabir b. Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) having forbidden the renting of land,21,115,,,,,,حماد بن زید نے ہمیں مطروراق سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے عطاء سے اور انہوں نے حضرت جابر بن عبداللہ رض,3916,
3917,1536.12,"Jabir b. Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:He who has land should cultivate it himself, but if he does not cultivate it himself, then he should let his brother cultivate it",21,116,,,,,,"مہدی بن میمون نے ہمیں حدیث بیان کی ،  کہا :  ہمیں مطروراق نے عطاء سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے حضرت ج",3917,
3918,1536.13,"Jabir b. Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) reported some of the Companions of Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) had surplus of land. Thereupon Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) said:He, who has surplus land (in his possession) should cultivate it, or he should lend it to his brother for benefit, but if he refuses to accept it, he should retain it",21,117,,,,,,"اوزاعی نے عطاء سے اور انہوں نے حضرت جابر بن عبداللہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی ،  انہوں نے کہا :  رسول",3918,
3919,1536.14,Jabir b. Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) having forbidden taking of rent or share of land,21,118,,,,,,"بکیر بن اخنس نے عطاء سے اور انہوں نے حضرت جابر بن عبداللہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی ،  انہوں نے کہا :",3919,
3920,1536.15,"Jabir (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:He who has land should cultivate it, but if he does not find it possible to cultivate it, or finds himself helpless to do so, he should lend it to his Muslim brother, but he should not accept rent from him",21,119,,,,,,عبدالملک نے ہمیں عطاء سے حدیث بیان کی اور انہوں نے حضرت جابر رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی ،  انہوں نے کہ,3920,
3921,1536.16,"Sulaiman b. Musa asked Ata':Did Jabir b. 'Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Apostle (ﷺ) as saying:"" He who has land should cultivate it himself, or let his brother cultivate it, and should not give on rent""? He said: Yes",21,120,,,,,,"ہمام نے حدیث بیان کی ،  کہا :  سلیمان بن موسیٰ نے عطاء سے سوال کیا اور کہا :  کیا آپ کو حضرت جابر بن",3921,
3922,1536.17,Jabir (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Apostle (ﷺ) having forbidden Mukhabara,21,121,,,,,,عمرو  ( بن دینار )  نے حضرت جابر رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی کہ نبی صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے مخابرہ  ( غلط,3922,
3923,1536.18,"Jabir b. Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) heard Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) say:He who has surplus of land should either cultivate it himself, or let his brother cultivate it, an should not sell it. I (the narrator) said to Sa'id: What does his statement"" do not sell it"" mean? Does it imply"" rent""? He said: Yes",21,122,,,,,,"سعید بن میناء نے ہمیں حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے کہا :  میں نے حضرت جابر بن عبداللہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے سن",3923,
3924,1536.19,"Jabir b. 'Abdullah reported:We used to cultivate land on rent during the lifetime of Allah's Apostle (ﷺ) and we got a share out of the grain left in the ears after threshing them and something unspecified. Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) said: He who has land should cultivate it or let his brother till it, otherwise he should leave it",21,123,,,,,,"زہیر نے ہمیں حدیث بیان کی ،  کہا :  ابوزبیر نے ہمیں حضرت جابر رضی اللہ عنہ سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں ",3924,
3925,1536.20,"Jabir b. Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) reported:We used to get land (on rent) during the lifetime of Allah's Messeuge, (ﷺ) with a share of one-third or one-fourth (of the produce from the land irrigated) with the help of canals. Thereupon Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) stood up (to address) and said: HRe who has land should cultivate it, and if he does not cultivate it, he should lend it to his brother, and if he does not lend it to his brother, he should then retain it",21,124,,,,,,"ہشام بن سعد نے مجھے حدیث بیان کی کہ انہیں ابوزبیر مکی نے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے کہا :  میں نے حضرت",3925,
3926,1536.21,"Jabir (Allah he pleased with him) reported:I heard Allah's Apostle (ﷺ) as saying: He who has (surplus) land should donate it (to others), or lend it",21,125,,,,,,"ابو عوانہ نے ہمیں سلیمان  ( اعمش )  سے حدیث بیان کی ،  کہا :  ہمیں ابوسفیان  ( طلحہ بن نافع )  نے حض",3926,
3927,1536.22,"This hadith has been narrated on the authority of A'mash with the same chain of transmitters, but with a slight change of words",21,126,,,,,,"عمار بن رُزَیق نے اعمش سے اسی سند کے ساتھ یہی حدیث بیان کی ،  البتہ انہوں نے کہا :   "" وہ اسے کاشت ک",3927,
3928,1536.23,"Jabir b. `Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) reportedthat Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) had forbidden renting of land. Bukair (one of the narrators) said:Nafi` reported to me that he heard Ibn `Umar (Allah be pleased with them) saying: We usedto give land on rent; we then abandoned this practice when we heard the hadith of Rafi` b. Khadij",21,127,,,,,,بکیر نے حدیث بیان کی کہ انہیں عبداللہ بن ابی سلمہ نے نعمان بن ابی عیاش سے حدیث بیان کی اور انہوں نے ,3928,
3929,1536.24,Jabir (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbidding the selling (renting of) uncultivated land for two years or three,21,128,,,,,,"ابوزبیر نے حضرت جابر رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی ،  انہوں نے کہا :  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے خال",3929,
3930,1536.25,"Jabir (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Apostle (ﷺ) forbidding selling of (produce) in advance for two years, and in the narmtion of Ibu Abd Shaiba (the words are):"" Selling of the fruits (on the tree) in advance for two years",21,129,,,,,,"سعید بن منصور ،  ابوبکر بن ابی شیبہ ،  عمرو ناقد اور زہیر بن حرب نے کہا :  ہمیں سفیان بن عیینہ نے حم",3930,
3931,1544,"Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) as saying:He who has land should cultivate it or lend it to his brother, but if he refuses, he should retain his land",21,130,,,,,,"حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے ،  انہوں نے کہا :  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا :  ",3931,
3932,1536.26,"Jabir b. Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) reported:I heard Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbidding Muzabana, and Huqul. Jabir b. Abdullah (Allah be pleased with them) said: Muzabana means the selling of fruits for dry dates and Huqul is the renting of land",21,131,,,,,,حضرت جابر بن عبداللہ رضی اللہ عنہ نے خبر دی کہ انہوں نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم سے سنا ،  آپ مز,3932,
3933,1545,Abu Huraira (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbidding Muhaqala and Muzabana,21,132,,,,,,"حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے ،  انہوں نے کہا :  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے محاقلہ اور",3933,
3934,1546,Abu Sa'id al-Khudri (Allah be pleased with him) reported Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) having forbidden Mazabana and Muhaqala. Muzibana means the buying of fruits on the trees and Muhaqala is the renting of land,21,133,,,,,,"حضرت ابوسعید خدری رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں :  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے مزابنہ اور محاقلہ سے منع ",3934,
3935,1547.01,"Zaid b. Amr reported:I heard Ibn Umar (Allah be pleased with them) say: We did not see any harm in renting of the land, but as the first year was over Rafi' alleged Allah's Apostle (ﷺ) having forbidden that",21,134,,,,,,"حماد بن زید نے ہمیں عمرو  ( بن دینار )  سے خبر دی ،  انہوں نے کہا :  میں نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عن",3935,
3936,1547.02,"This hadith has been narrated on the authority of Amr b. Dinar with the same chain of transmitters but (in) the hadith transmitted on the authority of 'Uyainah (the words are):"" We abandoned it (renting) on account of that",21,135,,,,,,سفیان  ( بن عیینہ )  ،  ایوب اور سفیان  ( ثوری )  سب نے عمرو بن دینار سے اسی سند کے ساتھ اسی کے مانن,3936,
3937,1547.03,"Ibn 'Umar (Allah be pleased with them) reported:Rafi forbade us from benefitting from our land (in the form of rent)",21,136,,,,,,"مجاہد سے روایت ہے ،  انہوں نے کہا :  حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ نے کہا :  رافع رضی اللہ عنہ نے ہماری ",3937,
3938,1547.04,"Nafi reported that Ibn Umar (Allah be pleased with them) rented his land during the lifetime of Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) and during the caliphate of Abu Bakr and that of Umar and that of Uthman (Allah be pleased with them) and during the early period of Muawiya's caliphate until at the end of Muawiya's reign, it reached him (Ibn 'Umar) that Rafi b. Khadij (Allah be pleased with him) narratted (a hadith) in which (there was a decree) of prohibition by Allah's Apostle (ﷺ). He (Ibn 'Umar) went to him (Rafi b. Khadij) and I was with him and he asked him, whereupon he said:Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) used to forbid the renting of land. So Ibn Umar (Allah be pleased with them) abandoned it, and subsequently whenever he was asked about it, he said: Rafi b. Khadij (Allah be pleased with him) alleged that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade it",21,137,,,,,,یزید بن زریع نے ہمیں ایوب سے خبر دی اور انہوں نے نافع سے روایت کی کہ رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے,3938,
3939,1547.05,"This hadith has been narrated on the authority of Ayyub and he made an addition in the hadith narrated by Ibn Ulayya in which he said:Ibn Umar abandoned it afterwards and he did not rent it (the land)",21,138,,,,,,حماد بن زید اور اسماعیل  ( ابن علیہ )  دونوں نے ایوب سے اسی سند کے ساتھ اسی کے مانند حدیث بیان کی او,3939,
3940,1547.06,"Nafi reported:I went to Rafi b. Khadij in the company of Ibn 'Umar (All be pleased with them) until he (Ibn 'Umar) came to him at Balat (a place near Prophet's Mosque at Medina) and he (Rafi b. Khadij) informed him that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) had forbidden the renting of land",21,139,,,,,,"عبیداللہ نے ہمیں نافع سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے کہا :  میں حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ کے ساتھ حضرت ",3940,
3941,1547.07,"Nafi, reported from Ibn Umar (Allah be pleated with them) that he came to Rafi and he narrated this hadith from Allah's Apostle (ﷺ)",21,140,,,,,,حکم نے نافع سے اور انہوں نے حضرت ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی کہ وہ حضرت رافع رضی اللہ عنہ کے پا,3941,
3942,1547.08,"Nafi, reported that Ibn Umar (Allah be pleased with them) used to rent the land, and that he was conveyed the hadith transmitted on the authority of Rafi b. Khadij. He (the narrator) said:He then went to him along with me. He (Rafi) narrated from some of his uncles in which it was mentioned that Allah's Apostle (ﷺ) forbade the renting of land. Ibn 'Umar (Allah be pleased with them) then abandoned this practice of renting",21,141,,,,,,"حسین بن حسن بن یسار نے ہمیں حدیث بیان کی ،  کہا :  ہمیں ابن عون نے نافع سے حدیث بیان کی کہ حضرت ابن ",3942,
3943,1547.09,This hadith has been narrated through another chain of transmitters,21,142,,,,,,"یزید بن ہارون نے کہا :  ہمیں ابن عون نے اسی سند کے ساتھ حدیث بیان کی اور کہا :  انہوں نے اپنے بعض چچ",3943,
3944,1547.10,"Salim b. Abdullah reported that AbduUah b. Umar (Allah be pleased with them) used to give land on rent until (this news) reached him that Rafi b. Khadij Ansari used to forbid the renting of land. Abdullah met him and said:Ibn Khadij, what is this that you narrate from Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) pertaining to renting of land? Rafi b. Khadij said to Abdullah: I heard it from two uncles of mine and they had participated in the Battle of Badr who narrated to the members of the family that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade the renting of land. Abdullah said: I knew it that the land was rented during the lifetime of Allah's Messenger (ﷺ). Abdullah then apprehended that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) might have said something new in this connection (in regard to prohibition of renting) which I failed to know. So he abandoned the renting of land",21,143,,,,,,سالم بن عبداللہ نے خبر دی کہ حضرت عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہ اپنی زمینیں کرائے پر دیتے تھے حتی کہ ا,3944,
3945,1548.01,"Rafi b. Khadij (Allah be pleased with him) reported:We used to give on rent land during the lifetime of Allah's Messenger (ﷺ). We rented it on the share of one-third or one-fourth of the (produce) along with a definite quantity of corn. One day a person from among my uncles came to us and said: Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade us this act which was a source of benefit to us, but the obedience to Allah and to His Messenger (ﷺ) is more beneficial to us. He forbade us that we should rent land with one-third or one-fourth of (the produce) and the corn of a measure, and he commanded the owner of land that he should cultivate it or let it be cultivated by other (persons) but he showed disapproval of renting it or anything besides it",21,144,,,,,,اسماعیل بن علیہ نے ہمیں ایوب سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے یعلیٰ بن حکیم سے ،  انہوں نے سلیمان بن یسار,3945,
3946,1548.02,"Rafi b. Khadij (Allah be pleased with him) reported:We used to give land on rent, and we rented it on one-third or one-fourth share. The rest of the hadith is the same",21,145,,,,,,"حماد بن زید نے ہمیں ایوب سے خبر دی ،  انہوں نے کہا :  یعلیٰ بن حکیم نے میری طرف لکھا ،  انہوں نے کہا",3946,
3947,1548.03,Another chain narrated the same as the above hadith,21,146,,,,,,ابن ابی عروبہ نے یعلیٰ بن حکیم سے اسی سند کے ساتھ اسی کے مانند روایت بیان کی,3947,
3948,1548.04,"This hadith has been narrated on the authority of Rafi' b. Khadij with the same chain of transmitters, but in it no mention is made of some of his uncles",21,147,,,,,,جریر بن حازم نے یعلیٰ بن حکیم کی اسی سند کے ساتھ روایت کی ،  انہوں نے  ( سلیمان کے واسطے سے )  رافع ,3948,
3949,1548.05,"Rafi (Allah be pleased with him) reported that Zuhair b. Rafi (who was his uncle) came to me and said:Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade a practice which was useful for us. I said: What is this? (I believe) that whatrver Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) says is absolutely true. He (Zuhair) said that he (the Holy Prophet) asked me: What do you do with your cultivable lands? I said: Allah's Messenger, we rent those irrigated by canals for dry dates or barley. He said: Don't do that. Cultivate them or let them be cultivated (by others) or retain them yourself",21,148,,,,,,ابوعمرو اوزاعی نے مجھے رافع بن خدیج رضی اللہ عنہ کے آزاد کردہ غلام ابونجاشی سے حدیث بیان کی اور انہو,3949,
3950,1548.06,"This hadith has been transmitted on the authority of Rafi from the Prophet (ﷺ) about this, but he did not make mention of his uncle Zuhair",21,149,,,,,,عکرمہ بن عمار نے ابونجاشی سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت رافع رضی اللہ عنہ سے اور انہوں نے نبی صلی اللہ علیہ وس,3950,
3951,1547.11,"Hanzala b. Qais reported that he asked Rafi b. Khadij (Allah be pleased with him) about renting of land, whereupon he said:Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade the renting of land. I said: Is it forbidden (even if it is paid) in gold (dinar) and silver (dirham)? Thereupon he said: If it is paid in gold and silver, there is no harm in it",21,150,,,,,,امام مالک نے ربیعہ بن ابی عبدالرحمٰن سے اور انہوں نے حنظلہ بن قیس سے روایت کی کہ انہوں نے حضرت رافع ,3951,
3952,1547.12,"Hanzala b. Qais al-Ansri reported:I asked Rafi' b. Khadij about the renting of land for gold and silver, whereupon he said: There is no harm in it for the people let out land situated near canals and at the ends of the streamlets or portion of fields. (But it so happened) that at times this was destroyed and that was saved. whereas (on other occasions) this portion was saved and the other was destroyed and thus no rent was payable to the people (who let out lands) but for this one (which was saved). It was due to this that he (the Holy Prophet) prohibited it. But if there is something definite and reliable (e. g. money). there is no harm in it",21,151,,,,,,"اوزاعی نے ہمیں ربیعہ بن ابی عبدالرحمٰن سے حدیث بیان کی ،  کہا :  مجھے حنظلہ بن قیس انصاری نے حدیث سن",3952,
3953,1547.13,"Hanzala reported that he heard Rafi' b. Khadij (Allah be pleased with him) say:We were the major agriculturists of the Ansar and so we let out land (saying): The produce of this (part of land) would be ours and (the produce) of that would be theirs. But it so happened that at times this (land) gave harvest, but the other one produced nothing. So he (the Holy Prophet) forbade this. But so far as the payment in silver (dirham, a coin) is concerned, he did not forbid",21,152,,,,,,سفیان بن عیینہ نے ہمیں یحییٰ بن سعید سے حدیث بیان کی ،  انہوں نے حنظلہ زُرَقی سے روایت کی کہ انہوں ن,3953,
3954,1547.14,This hadith has been narrated on the authority of Yahya b. Sa'id with the same chain of transmitters,21,153,,,,,,حماد اور یزید بن ہارون نے یحییٰ بن سعید سے اسی سند کے ساتھ اسی کے ہم معنی حدیث بیان کی,3954,
3955,1549.01,"Abdullah b. al Sa'ib reported:I asked Abdullah b. Ma'qil about Muzara'a (cultivating land on share basis in the produce). He said: Thabit b. Dahhak informed me that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade Muzara'a as Ibn Abu Shaiba forbade it with a slight change of words. He (the narrator) said: I asked Ibn Ma'qil but he did not name 'Abdullah",21,154,,,,,,"یحییٰ بن یحییٰ نے کہا :  ہمیں عبدالواحد بن زیاد نے خبر دی ،  نیز ابوبکر بن ابی شیبہ نے کہا :  ہمیں ع",3955,
3956,1549.02,"Abdullah b. al-Sa'ib reported:We visited 'Abdullah b. Ma'qil and asked him about sharing of crops, whereupon he said: Thabit alleged that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) forbade Muzara'a and commanded leasing it out on rent (for money) and said: There is no harm in it",21,155,,,,,,"ابوعوانہ نے ہمیں سلیمان شیبانی سے خبر دی ،  انہوں نے عبداللہ بن سائب سے روایت کی ،  انہوں نے کہا :  ",3956,
3957,1550.01,"Mujahid said to Tiwus:Come along with me to Ibn Rafi b. Khadij in order to listen from him the hadith transmitted on the authority of his father (pertaining to the renting of land) from Allah's Apostle (ﷺ). He (Tawus) scolded him and said: By Allah, it I were to know that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) had forbidden it, I would have never done it. But it has been narrated to me by one who has better knowledge of it amongst them (and he meant Ibn 'Abbas) that Allah's Messenger (ﷺ) said: It is better if a person lends, his land to his brother (for cultivation) than that he gets recognised rent on it",21,156,,,,,,"حماد بن زید نے ہمیں عمرو  ( بن دینار )  سے خبر دی کہ مجاہد نے طاوس سے کہا :  ہمارے ساتھ حضرت رافع بن",3957,
3958,1550.02,"Tawus reported that he let out his land on rent, whereupon Amr said:I said to him: Abu Abd al-Rahrman, I wish if you abandon this renting of land, for they alleged that Allah's Apostle (ﷺ) forbade Mukhabara. He siad: Amr, one who has informed me has the best knowledge of it among them (he meant Ibn Abbas). (He said) that Allah's Apostle (ﷺ) did not prohibit it altogether, but said: Lending of land by one among you to his brother is better for him than getting a specified amount of produce from it",21,157,,,,,,سفیان نے ہمیں عمرو اور ابن طاوس سے حدیث بیان کی اور انہوں نے طاوس سے روایت کی کہ وہ  ( نقدی کے عوض ),3958,
3959,1550.03,A hadith like this has been transmitted on the authority of Ibn Abbas (Allah be pleased with them),21,158,,,,,,ایوب ،  سفیان ،  ابن جریج اور شعبہ سب نے عمرو بن دینار سے ،  انہوں نے طاوس سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابن ع,3959,
3960,1550.04,"Ibn Abbas (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Apostle (ﷺ) as saying:If one among you lets out land to his brother, that is better for him than if he receives such and such (the definite thing). Ibn 'Abbis (Allah be pleased with them) said: It is Haql, and in the parlance of the Ansr it is Muhaqala",21,159,,,,,,معمر نے ابن طاوس سے ،  انہوں نے اپنے والد سے اور انہوں نے حضرت ابن عباس رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت کی کہ ,3960,
3961,1550.05,"Ibn Abbas (Allah be pleased with them) reported Allah's Apostle (ﷺ) as saying:He who has land, it is better for him that he should let it out to his brother",21,160,,,,,,عبدالملک بن زید نے طاوس سے ،  انہوں نے حضرت ابن عباس رضی اللہ عنہ سے اور انہوں نے نبی صلی اللہ علیہ ,3961,
